The paper focuses on querying data stored in a blockchain database, which is a core aspect of database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework that employs verifiable queries to guarantee the results' integrity, which falls under the category of security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes new indexes and data structures to improve query processing efficiency, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the storage and computing costs of the user, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC).
